GSD_T_PROJECT_DIR` was unset and `payload.cwd` was absent. `process.cwd()` for a Claude Code Stop/UserPromptSubmit hook is the directory the user launched `claude` from. When two parallel Claude Code sessions ran in different projects (`/Users/david/projects/GSD-T` and `/Users/david/projects/Move-Zoom-Recordings-to-GDrive`), the SAME node-runtime hook process resolved to whichever project the hook inherited via cwd — frames cross-talked. Concrete misroute: GSD-T orchestrator's NDJSON written into `Move-Zoom-Recordings-to-GDrive/.gsd-t/transcripts/in-session-800d4b3b-….ndjson` (verified 2026-05-07 11:30 — content was THIS session's banners, file was the wrong project's transcripts dir). **Fix** (2 new private fns + reordered `_resolveProjectDir`): `_slugFromTranscriptPath` extracts the directory-name slug from `~/.claude/projects/{slug}/{sid}.jsonl`; rejects paths outside that root. `_slugToProjectDir` DFS-walks the filesystem from `/`, greedily consuming `-`-separated tokens as directory names; first leaf where `.gsd-t/` exists wins. Disambiguates literal-hyphen project names (`Move-Zoom-Recordings-to-GDrive`) by consulting the disk — disk is the oracle. Rejects slugs containing `..`, `/`, `\\\\`, `\\0`, or not starting with `-`. New priority: env → transcript_path slug → `payload.cwd` → cwd walk-up. Walk-up emits a one-line stderr warning so future misroutes are diagnosable. **Reproduction-first**: wrote `test/m53b-conversation-routing.test.js` BEFORE touching the hook — confirmed the failing scenario, then fixed. **Tests** (`test/m53b-conversation-routing.test.js`, new, 16 cases): happy-path slug-decode beats wrong cwd, parallel-session no-cross-talk, literal-hyphen disambiguation, non-GSD-T target → fallthrough, path-traversal slug rejection, env-priority preservation, UserPromptSubmit also routes by transcript_path, plus 8 unit-level helper tests (slug rejection: not starting with `-`, contains `..`, contains `/`, contains NUL, decoded paths don't exist; happy-path direct decode; `_slugFromTranscriptPath` extracts and rejects). **Adversarial Red Team** (`test/m53b-conversation-routing-redteam.test.js`, new, 7 tests): three broken `_resolveProjectDir` variants (A: walk-up only ignores transcript_path → violates I1 own-project, also fails on parallel-cwd misroute scenario; B: naive `-`→`/` decode without `.gsd-t/` existence check → violates I2 existence + violates I1 on literal-hyphen names; C: literal-slug-as-path returns `~/.claude/projects/{slug}` → violates I3 slug-decoded + I1 own-project), each `assert.throws` with the exact invariant ID; two positive controls replay the real `_resolveProjectDir` against both projA (clean name) and projB (literal-hyphen) on the same fixture, both pass all four invariants. **Journey spec** (`e2e/journeys/conversation-routing.spec.ts`, new, 3 tests): spawns the real hook process via `child_process.spawnSync` twice with two `transcript_path` values pointing at slugs encoding two different fake projects under a fake `$HOME`; asserts each NDJSON lands in the matching project (no cross-talk), the neutral-cwd never grows a `.gsd-t/transcripts/` (proves walk-up did not fire), slug-pointing-at-non-GSD-T-dir falls through to cwd (existence check enforced), slug-as-literal-path-attack does NOT plant a transcripts dir at `~/.claude/projects/{slug}/.gsd-t/`. Manifest entry added to `.gsd-t/journey-manifest.json` (covers=[] — hook-source isn't viewer source, so coverage tool ignores; entry exists for catalogue completeness). `gsd-t check-coverage` still reports `OK: 20 listeners, 14 specs`. **Verification**: full unit suite **2226/2226 pass** (vs 2210 baseline; +16 routing + 7 redteam = +23, zero regressions). Playwright `e2e/journeys/` **16/16 pass** (vs 13 baseline; +3 conversation-routing). The 2 pre-existing flakes (`event-stream.test.js` `entry has command=null` + `watch-progress-writer.test.js` `writer_shim_safe_empty_agent_id`) remain unchanged — both pass cleanly when `GSD_T_COMMAND` / `GSD_