iagnosable. **Reproduction-first**: wrote `test/m53b-conversation-routing.test.js` BEFORE touching the hook — confirmed the failing scenario, then fixed. **Tests** (`test/m53b-conversation-routing.test.js`, new, 16 cases): happy-path slug-decode beats wrong cwd, parallel-session no-cross-talk, literal-hyphen disambiguation, non-GSD-T target → fallthrough, path-traversal slug rejection, env-priority preservation, UserPromptSubmit also routes by transcript_path, plus 8 unit-level helper tests (slug rejection: not starting with `-`, contains `..`, contains `/`, contains NUL, decoded paths don't exist; happy-path direct decode; `_slugFromTranscriptPath` extracts and rejects). **Adversarial Red Team** (`test/m53b-conversation-routing-redteam.test.js`, new, 7 tests): three broken `_resolveProjectDir` variants (A: walk-up only ignores transcript_path → violates I1 own-project, also fails on parallel-cwd misroute scenario; B: naive `-`→`/` decode without `.gsd-t/` existence check → violates I2 existence + violates I1 on literal-hyphen names; C: literal-slug-as-path returns `~/.claude/projects/{slug}` → violates I3 slug-decoded + I1 own-project), each `assert.throws` with the exact invariant ID; two positive controls replay the real `_resolveProjectDir` against both projA (clean name) and projB (literal-hyphen) on the same fixture, both pass all four invariants. **Journey spec** (`e2e/journeys/conversation-routing.spec.ts`, new, 3 tests): spawns the real hook process via `child_process.spawnSync` twice with two `transcript_path` values pointing at slugs encoding two different fake projects under a fake `$HOME`; asserts each NDJSON lands in the matching project (no cross-talk), the neutral-cwd never grows a `.gsd-t/transcripts/` (proves walk-up did not fire), slug-pointing-at-non-GSD-T-dir falls through to cwd (existence check enforced), slug-as-literal-path-attack does NOT plant a transcripts dir at `~/.claude/projects/{slug}/.gsd-t/`. Manifest entry added to `.gsd-t/journey