{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Rdz7Rfoj1KLSBLuasLg5p2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Contract: cli-build-coverage\n2\t\n3\tStatus: DRAFT (flips to STABLE at verify)\n4\tVersion: 0.1.0 (→ 1.0.0 STABLE)\n5\tOwner: m57-d1-build-coverage-check\n6\tConsumers: commands/gsd-t-verify.md (FAIL-blocking gate), `gsd-t build-coverage` CLI\n7\t\n8\t## Purpose\n9\t\n10\tDetect new top-level paths added in a milestone's commit range that no CI build\n11\tartifact references — the TimeTracking v1.10.12 failure class (new `hooks/` dir\n12\tcommitted, absent from Dockerfile `COPY`, shipped broken while verify passed).\n13\t\n14\t## API\n15\t\n16\t```\n17\tcheckBuildCoverage({ projectDir, baseRef, headRef }) → {\n18\t  ok: boolean,\n19\t  missing: string[],          // top-level paths not referenced by any CI artifact\n20\t  checkedAgainst: string[],   // which CI artifacts were detected & scanned\n21\t  newPaths: string[],         // all new top-level paths in baseRef..headRef\n22\t  note?: string               // set when no CI artifacts exist (nothing to check)\n23\t}\n24\t```\n25\t\n26\t- `projectDir` (string, required) — project root.\n27\t- `baseRef` / `headRef` (string, optional) — git refs bounding the milestone\n28\t  commit range. **Default when omitted**: `HEAD~1..HEAD`. (Plan phase MAY refine\n29\t  to a milestone-tag heuristic; the fallback stays `HEAD~1..HEAD`.)\n30\t\n31\t## Detection Rules — a new top-level path is \"covered\" if referenced by ANY of:\n32\t\n33\t1. `Dockerfile` — a `COPY` or `ADD` directive whose source path includes the\n34\t   top-level segment (line-based scan; handles `COPY . .`, `COPY src/ ...`,\n35\t   multi-stage `COPY --from=`).\n36\t2. `cloudbuild.yaml` — appears in any `steps[].args` or an artifacts/copy path\n37\t   (line/regex scan; no YAML lib).\n38\t3. `.github/workflows/*.yml` — appears as a path in any workflow file.\n39\t\n40\t`COPY . .` (or `ADD . .`) covers everything → `missing` is empty regardless.\n41\t\n42\t## Exit Codes (CLI)\n43\t\n44\t| Code | Meaning |\n45\t|------|---------|\n46\t| 0 | `ok:true` — all new paths covered, OR no CI artifacts exist (`note` set) |\n47\t| 4 | `ok:false` — ≥1 new top-level path uncovered (`missing[]` non-empty) |\n48\t| 2 | usage error (bad args, not a git repo, bad refs) |\n49\t\n50\t## Defensive Behavior\n51\t\n52\t- No git repo / detached HEAD / identical refs → exit 2 with a clear message.\n53\t- No CI artifacts at all → `ok:true`, `note:\"no CI artifacts detected\"`, exit 0\n54\t  (nothing to be inconsistent with — this is not a failure).\n55\t- Empty diff → `ok:true`, `newPaths:[]`, exit 0.\n56\t\n57\t## Success Criterion Binding\n58\t\n59\tSC1: `checkBuildCoverage` on a fixture where a new `hooks/` dir is committed but\n60\tabsent from the Dockerfile `COPY` directives returns `ok:false`,\n61\t`missing:[\"hooks\"]`, CLI exit code 4.\n62\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHR3EZa9UC4cmTnEHjzNKh","session_id":"58ad06dd-2644-4e21-9536-13779b8ab76f","uuid":"2041dd59-6f69-473d-929e-966d396c96b6","timestamp":"2026-05-18T21:38:13.010Z","subagent_type":"general-purpose","task_description":"Validate M57 plan"}
